        "title": "How to merge/federate two OSGi containers?",
        "body": "<p>I have FUSE ESB Enterprise installed on two virtual machines. <\/p>\n\n<ol>\n<li><p>FUSE ESB OSGi container on Virtual Machine vm1, suppose three bundles installed:<\/p>\n\n<p>FuseESB:karaf@vm1>osgi:list<\/p>\n\n<p>251 A<\/p>\n\n<p>252 B<\/p>\n\n<p>253 C<\/p><\/li>\n<li><p>FUSE ESB OSGi container on Virtual Machine vm2, suppose three bundles installed:\nFuseESB:karaf@vm2>osgi:list<\/p>\n\n<p>251 A<\/p>\n\n<p>252 B<\/p>\n\n<p>253 C<\/p><\/li>\n<\/ol>\n\n<p>My goal is to combine or federate these two OSGi containers, so that the container on vm1 can see bundle B as well as all the other bundles from vm2. Also the container on vm2 can see bundle A as well as all the other bundles from vm1. That is, one container can access all the bundles from another container. <\/p>\n\n<p>By access I mean start/stop/update bundles and discover/consume services from another container.<\/p>\n\n<p>After federation, from vm1:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>FuseESB:karaf@vm1&gt;osgi:list\n\n251 A\n\n252 B\n\n253 C\n\n254 A'\n\n255 B'\n\n256 C'\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Because both containers have the same bundle named A, I am wondering if there is some mechanism to automatically rename A to A' to avoid name conflict. \nIs it possible to achieve this goal? Anyone can provide me some information about doing this?<\/p>\n",
